  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Ylläskaltio Hotel is on half board. A daily breakfast buffet is served daily from 7am to 10am with a selection of sweet and savoury options. A buffet dinner is served daily from 5pm to 7.30pm with a choice of starters mains and desserts. </p>
<p>Meals are served in the Ylläskaltio Restaurant - it's surrounded by glass so you get the most beautiful views of the snowy surroundings while you eat. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Whether you're here to hit the slopes, explore the Arctic Circle on a <a data-udi="umb://document/986da82374b54b72ac87e1894f0b812c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/986da82374b54b72ac87e1894f0b812c}" title="Reindeer Rides">reindeer drawn sleigh</a> or whizz around the fells on snowmobile, the Ylläskaltio Hotel is the perfect place to stay. The simple, modern hotel has been designed with lots of great facilities including a bar and restaurant.  Plus, it's located within walking distance of the centre of Äkäslompolo with direct access to the cross country ski tracks. </span></p>
<h2>Panoramic restaurant</h2>
<p><span>The large semi-circular restaurant has high ceilings and large windows, which create a really nice open space to enjoy your breakfast and dinner- the snowy views are an added bonus. The meals are inspired by the flavours of Lapland, however there is a variety of options to meet most tastes. Additionally, a cosy lobby bar can be found on the hotel's first floor, which serves a range of drinks. </span></p>
<h2>Sauna in every room</h2>
<p><span>When you're not enjoying the wide open runs of <a data-udi="umb://document/cc68d9ee210a4063af0a51552472263c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cc68d9ee210a4063af0a51552472263c}" title="Yllas">Ylläs</a> or snowmobiling through the wintery landscape, cosy up back at the hotel, have a drink in the bar or relax and make the most of the private sauna in your room - there's one in all of them. The rooms are simple and comfortable, and have all the amenities needed for a break in Lapland. There are two different room types available, a twin room - ideal for a couple or small family or if you're holidaying as a family, go for a family room - they have a mezzanine above the main room with two additional beds. </span></p>]]></description>
